status_message: Filmmakers created the centaur models using a technique where the pelts were "flocked," a laborious process by applying glue, sending an electrical charge through it, and then firing oppositely charged hairs at the model. It took the costume and prop departments eight months and a crew of more than forty people to get the job done. #HarryPotter #BehindTheScenes #CreatureVaultBook
